            "reviews": "“Bit Shifter is an outstanding throw back to gaming’s past while incorporating enough modern mechanics to make it highly accessible and fun to its target audience.”<br><a href=\"https://steamcommunity.com/linkfilter/?url=http://www.steamified.com/when-you-have-a-virus-you-need-a-bit-shifter/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"  >Steamified</a><br><br>“Plastic Games's new title takes on all comers with ease, offering a fully baked experience that impresses far more than the laughably incomplete tech demos that have made the service more of a scarlet letter than a viable business model.”<br><a href=\"https://steamcommunity.com/linkfilter/?url=http://www.slantmagazine.com/house/article/early-access-coasting-plastic-gamess-bit-shifter\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"  >Slant Magazine</a><br><br>“I really love the setting of the game, and I think it's a setting that would appeal to a lot of us nerdy types about being inside the 1's and 0's of our computers.”<br><a href=\"https://steamcommunity.com/linkfilter/?url=https://www.gamingonlinux.com/articles/deploy-robots-in-bit-shifter-a-3d-actionstrategy-game-now-on-linux-we-have-keys-to-give-away.6161/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"  >Gaming On Linux</a><br>",
